{"TopicId":153615,"ForumId":55,"TopicTitle":"I need a timer/stopwatch","CreatedByName":"Triop","CreatedById":145841,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-17T02:20:55Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Triop","CreatedById":145841,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-17T02:20:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo many mods, but I can\u0027t find a simple timer/stopwatch.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDid I missed it or is there no need ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Galileo","CreatedById":150430,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-17T02:31:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou could always use a cell phone of you have one.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI can\u0027t think of a need for one in game though\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Program Kerbal Space","CreatedById":169331,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-17T04:05:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere is a mod called \u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock\u0022 found\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/22809-12x-kerbal-alarm-clock-v3830-december-11/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EHere\u003C/a\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-12-17T04:05:34Z\u0022 title=\u002212/17/2016 04:05  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 17, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Program Kerbal Space\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"John FX","CreatedById":59415,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-17T10:24:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222890680\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022153615\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221481941255\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022145841\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Triop\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, Triop said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo many mods, but I can\u0027t find a simple timer/stopwatch.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDid I missed it or is there no need ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy thought is there is no need. All the things I need to do with time and keeping track of it are covered by Kerbal Alarm Clock.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat do you need one for?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Signo","CreatedById":103766,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-17T11:35:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you are looking for a way to read on screen the time to apoapsis, time to suicide burn and so on you can try with MechJeb.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Mechjeb (mod)\u0022\u003EMJ\u003C/abbr\u003E is like a swiss knife, jack of all trades.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}